President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key roles in his administration. Rufus Gifford, a former U.S. Ambassador to Denmark and Deputy Campaign Manager for Biden's presidential campaign, has been nominated for Chief of Protocol at the Department of State. Kathleen Miller, currently serving as the Administrative Assistant to the Secretary of the Army, has been nominated for Deputy Under Secretary of Defense (Comptroller). Larry Turner, who has been serving as Acting Inspector General of the U.S. Department of Labor, has been nominated for Inspector General at the Department of Labor. These nominations are subject to confirmation by the Senate.